•	fBodyBodyGyroJerkMag-mean()

•	fBodyBodyGyroJerkMag-std()

•	fBodyBodyGyroJerkMag-meanFreq()

mean(): Mean value
std(): Standard deviation
meanFreq(): Weighted average of the frequency components to obtain a mean frequency

Note the 'f' to indicate frequency domain signals. These signals were used to estimate variables of the feature vector for each pattern:   '-XYZ' is used to denote 3-axial signals in the X, Y and Z directions.

#Transformations:
--Read data files using read.table
--Change the activity and features files (column 2) into a character class 
--RowBind the x and y data frames, subject files and filter columns using the grep index for features file
--ColumnBind subject, activity and data into one data frames
--Use functions melt and dcast to reshape the final data.
